<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Information_rights_arm  Entity: Information_right  
   <express_ref linkend="information_rights:arm:Information_rights_arm.Information_right"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->

<ext_description linkend="Information_rights_arm.Information_right">
An information right defines what may or may not be done with an item of information in the sense of legal
rights and obligations.
<example number="1">Copyright is an information right.</example>
<example number="2">For the purposes of developing a new system, details of government furnished equipment may be made available to a particular project
team. The team may copy and use the information internally, but may not pass it on, either to a third part, or to another team, and must
destroy the information at the end of the contract.</example>
</ext_description>


